	<dd><a name="comment_963" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>NK</strong> replies:</em> "If anything it's the voters who have no right to complain." Well thats ot entirely true now is it? </p> <p>Yeah sure, you vote for the party which gets into government, then you should not be moaning, and if you are, perhaps you should of read their manifesto for a little longer then what the TV broadcasts allow for. </p> <p>If however, your party doesn't win, then you have as much right as the next person to complain.</p> <p>TL's comment is more accurate.<br />"If anyone doesn't have the right to complain about Government, it's the people that put them there."</p>
